    <element name="Metamorph" type="Class" source="Titans and Mortals" id="ID_TAM_CLASS_METAMORPH">
        <description>
            <p>A gnome ascends a cliff face when an earthquake threatens to plummet him to his death; in response, muscle snaps away from his forearm and digs its calcified ends into the rock, providing much-needed purchase.</p>
            <p class="indent">Verdant green tendrils strangle a disheveled goliath, as these vines tighten their embrace her jaw splits open at the base and shoots out caustic liquid, freeing her once the smoke clears.</p>
            <p class="indent">The victor of a duel appears clear once the heart of one is pierced, yet as triumph etches itself on one individual’s face, their head quickly ends up rolling along the ground, a secondary heart maintaining the life of the true victor.</p>
            <p class="indent">All of these are examples of Metamorphs, individuals that through one way or another have gained the ability to change their form as if it were clay, which they use to evolve at the drop of a hat to reverse their position of prey into that of a predator.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">QUICK BUILD</h5>
            <p>You can make a Metamorph quickly by following these suggestions. First, put your highest ability score in Constitution, followed by Dexterity or Charisma. Second, choose the Outlander background.</p>
            <h2>CLASS FEATURES</h2>
            <p>As an Metamorph, you gain the following class features.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">HIT POINTS</h5>
            <ul class="unstyled">
                <li><strong>Hit Dice:</strong> 1d12 per Metamorph level</li>
                <li><strong>Hit Points at 1st Level:</strong> 12 + your Constitution modifier</li>
                <li><strong>Hit Points at Higher Levels:</strong> 1d12 (or 7) + your Constitution modifier per Metamorph level after 1st</li>
            </ul>
            <h5 class="caption">PROFICIENCIES</h5>
            <ul class="unstyled mb">
                <li><strong>Armor:</strong> Light armour, Medium armour</li>
                <li><strong>Weapons:</strong> Simple weapons</li>
                <li><strong>Tools:</strong> None</li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="unstyled">
                <li><strong>Saving Throws:</strong> Constitution, Charisma</li>
                <li><strong>Skills:</strong> Choose three from Acrobatics, Animal Handling, Athletics, Deception, Intimidation, Insight, Investigation, Nature, Perception, Stealth, and Survival</li>
            </ul>
            <h5 class="caption">EQUIPMENT</h5>
            <p>You start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><i>(a)</i> scale mail or <i>(b)</i> leather armour</li>
                <li>any simple melee weapon</li>
                <li><i>(a)</i> light crossbow and 20 bolts or <i>(b)</i> shortbow and 20 arrows</li>
                <li><i>(a)</i> a dungeoneer's pack or <i>(b)</i> an explorer's pack</li>
            </ul>
