    <element name="Adaptations" type="Class Feature" source="Titans and Mortals" id="ID_TAM_CLASS_FEATURE_METAMORPH_ADAPTATIONS">
        <description>
            <p>Beginning at 1st level, you gain the capability to learn aspects of the creatures you fight and defeat, forever incorporating their essence into yours.</p>
            <p class="indent">Choose 6 Adaptations from the list of Adaptations for which you meet the <strong>Prerequisites</strong>, you now add these 6 to your Dormant Adaptations and may have a number of Active Adaptations up to your limit, this limit increases as you level up per the Active Adaptations column of the Metamorph table. At the end of a short rest, you may swap a number of Active Adaptations equal to your Constitution Modifier for Dormant ones, or swap all of your Active Adaptations at the end of a long rest.</p>
            <p class="indent">Additionally at the end of a combat encounter for every creature you personally reduced to 0 hit points you may make a Constitution ability check of DC 8 + half of the creatures CR (rounded down), on a success choose an Adaptation for which the <strong>Source</strong> requirements are met by the slain creature and add it to your Dormant Adaptations. The level required in the <strong>Prerequisites</strong> of an Adaptation does not stop you from acquiring it through slaying a creature, it merely stops you from making an Active Adaptation instead of a Dormant one.</p>
            <p class="indent">Some of your features or Adaptations require your target to make a saving throw to resist the effects. The saving throw DC is calculated as follows:</p>
            <center>
				<p><strong>Metamorph save DC</strong> = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Constitution modifier</p>
            </center>
        </description>
